Day 4 of my Java learning journey.

Today I learned how things actually work inside memory.

I understood the concept of a “black box” in programming — how we often use things without worrying about internal complexity, but still need a basic idea of what’s happening.

Also explored how positive and negative values are stored in memory, along with how floating-point values are represented.

It’s interesting to see what happens behind the scenes when we write even simple code.

Still learning slowly, but concepts are getting clearer.

